free_txt: .Corrections are made for
- multiple scattering;
- attenuation;
- neutron source contamination.
based on JENDL-3. In case that JENDL-3 would produce
double differential neutron emission spectrum in
drastic disagreement with the measured one, the
correction can be failed and the adoption of raw data
is recommended by authors.
.Correction factor are calculated using evaluated data,
however, they are still primitive. Calculation of
correction factors should be carried out again after
new version of evaluation would be published.
NE-213 liquid scintillator 25.4 cm in diameter
and 10.0 cm in length. The detector was shielded from
source and room scattered neutrons, a shadowbar
and different collimators. The source neutron flux was
monitored by another NE213 scintillator with 5.08 cm
diameter and 5.08 cm length, which was set at zero
degrees with respect to the deuteron beam line.
The intense 14 MeV neutron source
OKTAVIAN of Osaka University.
Less than 2 nsec pulsed neutrons were generated
at a repetition rate of 0.5 MHz. The angular distribu-
tion of the source neutron yield was known to within
2.4% from Al foil activation measurements.
Neutron flight path length was about 8.3 m.
